    <description>
LightCrosshair is a lightweight, high-performance crosshair overlay for competitive gaming on Windows 10/11.

## Features
- Custom crosshair builder with full shape control
- Integrated FPS overlay with ETW-style present telemetry and optional RTSS fallback
- Process-aware display color management (per-profile gamma/contrast/brightness)
- Modern profile workflow with immutable defaults
- Low CPU footprint optimized for gameplay
- Multi-monitor support with DPI awareness
- Screen recording detection for streaming/recording

## Requirements
- Windows 10 or later
- .NET 8.0 Windows Desktop Runtime (required for the current framework-dependent package)

## Installation
The 1.4.0 Chocolatey package is not final until release artifacts and checksums are approved and the package is pushed.

After installation, launch LightCrosshair from your Start Menu or find the executable in Program Files.
    </description>
    <summary>Lightweight gaming crosshair overlay with FPS counter and color management</summary>
    <releaseNotes>
v1.4.0 (May 2026): Candidate baseline for portable ZIP, Inno Setup, Chocolatey, WinGet, and PowerShell install script distribution. Package-manager channels are prepared only until final artifacts and checksums are approved. MSIX is intentionally excluded.

See https://github.com/PrimeBuild-pc/LightCrosshair/releases for full details.
    </releaseNotes>
